  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>Therapeutic management</measure>
    <time_frame>Baseline</time_frame>
    <description>Calculate the average time elapsed between the request for a molecular diagnosis by the ALS centre and the sending of the result. This will demonstrate the fluidity of the procedure and the ability to quickly inform the patient and the requesting clinician of the genetic status which will be essential to rapidly include patients in targeted gene therapy trials.</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>Integration of the molecular study into the routine work-up</measure>
    <time_frame>12 months</time_frame>
    <description>Compare the percentage of patients who have received genetic analysis to the number of new cases diagnosed in the ALS centres.</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
